Recently seen online:

http://www.fleen.com/archives/2007/10/15/some-things-of-note-plus-a-l...

&quot;If every cartoonist would agree to take their work offline
forever, we would all make fifteen times as much money. Weve done a
really stupid thing [by putting content online].&quot;

Rall is refering specifically to editorial cartoons here.

POD: 1996

Someone in the Association of American Editorial Cartoonists,
concerned about the effect the web might have on professional editorial
cartoonists, manages to push through a resolution condemning online
publication. Somewhat less probably, the members of the AAEC do not
imitate a herd of cats but get onboard with the resolution. Very few
of the AAEC members allow their work to be put up online.

Results?

My expectation is that online cartoons are a niche that will
be filled and if the AAEC members don't, someone else will.

