The online editorial cartoonists get a source for a cartoon or two at
AAEC's expense, and online comics continue, with non AAEC artists
getting more exposure.

<QUOTE PREVIOUSPOST="
&gt;         My expectation is that online cartoons are a niche that will
&gt; be filled and if the AAEC members don't, someone else will.
">

I agree with you.  More notably, the Web editorial cartoons may become
edgier than their newsprint-bound counterparts, mainly because the
artists are not actually bound to a specific group telling them what
to do.

Around here, newspaper sales are declining noticeably.  I believe one
of the reasons is that they are competing against cheaper sources such
as online news.
