Unless you engage in very heavy handed censorship, it is impossible.

This is a common economic fallicy that cartels actually work when you
have a large number of seperate actors in the cartel, and all it takes
is a few to break the cartel.

The few who think they can gain an advantage by breaking the cartel
will do so and the jig is up.

Interesting artical about economic fallicies and how they are commonly
held by voters in  the USA (and many other places).  You might hold
several of them, but you cannot get an economics paper published in a
respectable economics journal with any of them in the paper any more
than you can publish a physics paper with a flat earth basis.

http://www.reason.com/news/show/122019.html
